results.title:
FICCI FLO INDORE on Instagram: "*Trailblazer Awards 2025 – A Decade of Empowerment and Excellence* 

Dear FLO Indore Members,

It is with immense pride and joy that I share the success of the Trailblazer Awards 2025, a landmark event marking FLO Indore’s 10th anniversary. This grand celebration honored extraordinary women who have broken barriers and redefined success in their respective fields.

We were privileged to have  Shri Shankar Lalwani, Member of Parliament, Indore, as the Chief Guest who graced the event, adding to its prestige and Ms. Joyshree Das Verma, National President, FICCI FLO, as the Guest of Honor, reaffirming our commitment to empowering women.

The Trailblazer Awards were presented in three distinguished categories:
1- *Social Impact:* Recognizing women making significant societal contributions. Winners – Ms. Aarti Bisaria, Ms. Garvisha Barjatya Jain, Ms. Surbhi Manocha Chaudhary.

 *2- Unconventional Work:* Honoring women excelling in non-traditional fields. Winners – Ms. Pallavi Keskar, Ms. Saumya Upadhyay, Ms. Barkha Agarwal.

 *3- Exemplary Work in their Fields:* Celebrating professional excellence. Winners – Dr. Jyoti Bindal, Ar. Shruti Purohit, Ms. Ronika Gagneja Valecha.

In addition, special recognitions were given to Ms. Vandana Laddha ( *Pioneer Woman* ), Ms. Jasmine Lulla ( *She Leads* ), Dr. Dipti Jain ( *Soulpreneur* ), and Ms. RJ Sharda ( *Youth Icon of Indore).* 

The event also provided a platform for women entrepreneurs to showcase their businesses to an elite audience, including distinguished guests and city dignitaries. The evening was made even more vibrant with mesmerizing dance performances by FLO Indore members, embodying the spirit of joy, celebration, and empowerment.

I extend my heartfelt gratitude to each FLO Indore member for their continuous support and contribution. As we celebrate a decade of success, let us continue to uplift, inspire, and empower each other to lead and transform society.

Warm regards-
Ar. Vibha Jain Sethi
Chairperson
FLO Indore, 2024-25"
